<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef780657-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s2219"><num value="2219">§ 2219.</num><heading> Salaries; how paid</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Agriculture is authorized and directed to pay the salary of each employee from the roll of the bureau, independent division, or office in which the employee is working, and no other.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idef780658-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1907-03-04/ch2907">Mar. 4, 1907, ch. 2907</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/34/1280">34 Stat. 1280</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idef780659-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
